source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/mexican-tomato-jumble-20-5723299b4dab71b6668b4567
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @tomato mix{1%premium} in half and roughly chop the @coriander{3}. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm cubes (don't peel the nutritious skin).

Peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks). Toss the sweet potato and onion in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking tray{} in a single layer and cook on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20%minutes}.

> Tip: Everything is ready once it's nice and crispy at the edges.

Slice the @halloumi{1} into roughly ½cm slices.

Mix the @mexican spice{1.5} with the zest of half the @lime{1/2}(zested) and @olive oil{2%tsp}. Roll the lime firmly between your hand and the #work surface{} to loosen it up. Cut it in half and squeeze @lime juice{1%tsp} into the mixture along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Rub the mixture over the halloumi slices. Heat a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium heat with @olive oil{2%tsp}. Cook the halloumi for ~{2%minutes} on each side until just golden.

> Tip: Don't overcook them as they will become brittle and lose their wonderful texture.

In a #bowl{} toss the tomatoes with @lime juice{1/2%tsp}. Add in the coriander, roasted sweet potato and onion. Plate up with your halloumi slices on top.